The former Zimbabwe president had been battling ill health and was receiving treatment in Singapore. #Dstv403 JOHANNESBURG - Tributes are pouring in for former Zimbabwean revolutionary, politician and president, Robert Mugabe. Mugabe died aged 95 on Friday in Singapore after battling ill health. READ: Robert Mugabe dies aged 95 He served as Zimbabwean Prime Minister from 1980 to 1987 and then as President from 1987 to 2017. Mugabe was ousted from power in Zimbabwe. Several people took to social media to remember the former Zimbabwean President.